urlText: L2 and L3 Light rail services may be temporarily held at stops of partially closed due to a Police Operation
content:
On Sunday 21 January, L2 Randwick Line and L3 Kingsford Line light rail services may be impacted between 2.45pm and 3.30pm approximately due to road closures around Town Hall for a planned Police Operation protest march:
  • L2 and L3 services may be temporarily held at stops, or
  • L2 and L3 services may be temporarily partially closed between Town Hall and Circular Quay.
Impact to services and timings may change at the direction of NSW Police. Please check information screens at stops, listen to announcements and follow the direction of staff or Police on site, as necessary.
 
Allow extra travel time and use the Trip Planner for alternative transport options, including trains, buses or walking.
 
L1 Dulwich Hill Line light rail services should continue to run as per normal schedule.

For more details on ferry service changes and other transport options, visit the Australia Day event page.

urlText: Changes to M92 Parramatta to Sutherland bus route
content:
From Sunday 24 September, route M92 Parramatta to Sutherland will be split into two new routes:
  • 920 Parramatta-Bankstown
  • 960 Bankstown-Sutherland
Passengers travelling the full length of the route (Parramatta to Sutherland), will need to change buses at Bankstown.
  • 920 services depart from Bankstown Station Stand E
  • 960 services depart from Bankstown Station Stand B
All other stops remain the same.
 
For more information see the news story.
 
This change will improve journey time and reliability for passengers and will allow drivers to complete other routes impacted by driver shortages.
 
Plan your trip with Trip Planner or transport apps before you travel.

urlText: Service changes for Australia Day
content:
Ferries will be affected by exclusion zones on the harbour from 11.45am to 12.30pm and from 7.30pm to 9.45pm while Australia Day events take place on the water on Friday 26 January.
 
Ferries arriving/leaving the city between 11.10am and 12.30pm will not stop at Circular Quay. Ferries leaving Pyrmont between 11.10am and 11.55am will not stop at Circular Quay. To Pyrmont, ferries will not leave from Circular Quay between 11.27am and 12.42pm.
 
In the evening ferries will not run. The last service leaves Circular Quay at 7.12pm and Pyrmont at 6.40pm. Services resume with additional late-night ferries leaving Circular Quay at 10.12pm and 11.12pm, and from Pyrmont at 10.40pm and 11.40pm.
 
For more details on ferry service changes and other transport options, visit the Australia Day event page.

urlText: Service changes for Australia Day
content:
Ferries will be affected by exclusion zones on the harbour from 11.45am to 12.30pm and from 7.30pm to 9.45pm while Australia Day events take place on the water on Friday 26 January.
 
Manly ferries will not run during the morning exclusion zone, catch buses to travel between Manly and the city instead, additional route 170x buses will run between Manly and Wynyard. The last ferry leaves Circular Quay at 11.30am and the last ferry leaves Manly at 11.15am. Services resume from Circular Quay at
12.45pm and Manly at 12.30pm.
 
During the evening exclusion zone ferries will not stop at Circular Quay and will use Barangaroo wharf instead. Ferries leaving Manly between 7pm and 9.20pm will stop at Barangaroo. Ferries to Manly between 7.40pm and 9.10pm will leave from Barangaroo instead.
 
Ferries resume running between Manly and Circular Quay from 9.50pm.
 
For more details on ferry service changes and other transport options, visit the Australia Day event page.
